sentences: In 2002 he released his first solo album (the self-titled "Daniel Salomon") which produced several Israeli radio hits ("Better", "coming from pain")
In 2005, Salomon released his second solo album, "So Many Ways".
Salomon's third solo album – "Haifa 87" was released on August 2007 and generated a hit single, "Could It Be".
In 2007, Salomon worked on "Shfuyim" (Sane) by Shlomo Artzi.
Salomon won the "Composer of the year" award from the Israeli Composers' Society.
Aviv Geffen – white nights, memento mori, jouerny diary, with time
